In[44]:
def show_batch(image_batch, label_batch, class_indices):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
    for i in range(min(9, len(image_batch))):
        ax = plt.subplot(3, 3, i + 1)
        plt.imshow(image_batch[i])
        class_idx = np.argmax(label_batch[i])
        class_name = list(class_indices.keys())[list(class_indices.values()).index(class_idx)]
        plt.title(class_name)
        plt.axis("off")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

In[55]:
def predict_image(image_path, model, class_names):
    img = image.load_img(image_path, target_size=(img_width, img_height))
    img_array = image.img_to_array(img)
    img_array = np.expand_dims(img_array, axis=0)  # Ajouter une dimension pour batch
    img_array /= 255.0  # Normaliser les valeurs des pixels

    predictions = model.predict(img_array)
    predicted_class = np.argmax(predictions, axis=1)[0]
    confidence = np.max(predictions) * 100  # Confiance en la prdiction (en %)

    return class_names[predicted_class], confidence, img

# Rcuprer tous les fichiers d'images dans le dossier de test
test_images = []
for category in os.listdir(test_dir):
    category_path = os.path.join(test_dir, category)
    if os.path.isdir(category_path):  # Si c'est un dossier de catgorie
        for img_name in os.listdir(category_path):
            img_path = os.path.join(category_path, img_name)
            if img_name.lower().endswith(('png', 'jpg', 'jpeg')):
                test_images.append(img_path)

# Mlanger les images de manire alatoire
random.shuffle(test_images)

    plt.subplot(4, 4, i+1)  # 4x4 grille pour 16 images
    plt.imshow(img)
    plt.title(f"Prdiction: {predicted_class}\n{confidence:.2f}%", color='green')
    plt.axis('off')

from tensorflow.keras.applications import ResNet50
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import GlobalAveragePooling2D, Dense, Dropout
from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import Adam

# Taille d'entre souhaite
img_width, img_height = 64, 64

# Charger ResNet50 avec input_shape=(64, 64, 3)
base_model = ResNet50(
    weights='imagenet',
    include_top=False,
    input_shape=(img_width, img_height, 3)
)

# Geler toutes les couches
for layer in base_model.layers:
    layer.trainable = False

# Dgeler les 26 dernires couches
for layer in base_model.layers[-26:]:
    layer.trainable = True

# Construire le modle
model = Sequential([
    base_model,
    GlobalAveragePooling2D(),
    Dense(256, activation='relu'),
    Dropout(0.5),
    Dense(6, activation='softmax')  # 6 classes
])

# Compiler
model.compile(
    optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=1e-5),
    loss='categorical_crossentropy',
    metrics=['accuracy']
)

# Rsum
model.summary()

from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix
import seaborn as sns
import numpy as np

# Prdictions
validation_generator.reset()
y_true = []
y_pred = []

for _ in range(validation_generator.samples // validation_generator.batch_size):
    x_batch, y_batch = next(validation_generator)
    pred = model.predict(x_batch)
    y_true.extend(np.argmax(y_batch, axis=1))
    y_pred.extend(np.argmax(pred, axis=1))

# Matrice
cm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)
class_names = list(train_generator.class_indices.keys())

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues',
            xticklabels=class_names, yticklabels=class_names)
plt.xlabel('Prdiction')
plt.ylabel('Rel')
plt.title('Matrice de confusion')
plt.show()
